<p class=""><h2>Key Challenges in the Lotus Core Extract Market</h2><ul>    <li><strong>Regulatory Compliance:</strong> The lotus core extract industry faces stringent regulations regarding product safety and labeling. Navigating these regulations can be complicated, leading to increased costs and time delays for manufacturers.</li>    <li><strong>Supply Chain Issues:</strong> The procurement of lotus cores is often dependent on environmental factors, making the supply chain vulnerable to disruptions. Natural disasters, climate change, and overharvesting can lead to scarcity and fluctuation in raw material prices.</li>    <li><strong>Quality Control:</strong> Maintaining the consistency and quality of lotus extracts can be challenging. Variations in growing conditions and processing methods can affect the efficacy and reliability of the final products, which may tarnish brand reputation.</li>    <li><strong>Market Awareness:</strong> Despite the numerous benefits of lotus extracts, consumer awareness remains relatively low. This lack of knowledge makes it difficult for manufacturers to fully capitalize on market potential, hindered by competition from more widely recognized botanical extracts.</li>    <li><strong>Formulation Challenges:</strong> Developers face difficulties in integrating lotus extracts into various product formats, such as cosmetics, dietary supplements, and beverages. Each format may require specific formulations to maintain the extract's efficacy and stability.</li></ul><h2>Potential Growth Opportunities in the Lotus Core Extract Market</h2><ul>    <li><strong>Health and Wellness Trends:</strong> Increasing consumer interest in natural and organic products provides a significant opportunity for the lotus core extract market. These extracts are packed with antioxidants and have anti-inflammatory properties, positioning them favorably in the health supplements sector.</li>    <li><strong>Expansion in Cosmetic Applications:</strong> The beauty indus